post_text: This is an update to the earlier message about returning to school this fall. After receiving guidance from the Governor's Office and DPI, we are in the process of creating a committee of stakeholders to create our local Health and Safety Plan. After this is plan is completed, the school board will review and approve it and it will be distributed to the public. Attached are the K12 Restart Guide that was released earlier this week that the Health and Safety Plan will be based on. As always, if you have any questions, please call the school. Thank you. https://5il.co/ibxl

post_text: I am pleased to announce that as we continue with a phased reopening, beginning Monday, July 6th, our weight room will re-open to the public. Thank you.

post_text:
Bank of North Dakota announced that its College SAVE 529 plan is sponsoring the EVERFI National Financial Bee, taking place April 20-30, 2020. The National Financial Bee is a first-of-its-kind nationwide financial literacy challenge for students in grades 7-12.

To participate in the National Financial Bee, students may complete five 15-minute modules before April 30. Upon completion of the modules, they can submit a 300- to 500-word essay highlighting what they learned. This qualifies students in grades 7-10 with an opportunity to win an EVERFI scholarship of $10,000, $6,000 or $4,000. North Dakota students in grades 7-12 receive the opportunity to be awarded one of two $529 scholarships from the College SAVE 529 plan. Students can visit bnd.nd.gov/financialbee to get started.

Dear PK-12 Families:

Mr. Wachter and Mr. Larson will be holding two online meetings on Tuesday, March 24th. During this time, we will do our best to answer any questions that you may have for the administration. If you would like to ask a question in advance, please feel free to call the school and we will record your question for the live meeting. If you are unable to get logged in during the meeting times, please know that we plan to continue having these online meetings as needed. Below is some key information for attending the meetings…

-Limits: We have a 100-person limit and a max of 40 minute meetings.

-Joining the Meeting: We will put a link on our website live feed, Facebook, and Twitter 10 minutes before the meetings begin. You will simply click the link, download Zoom, and then will be able to join the meeting.

-Times (Tuesday, March 24th): *3:00pm (link will be sent out at 2:50pm) *7:00pm (link will be sent out at 6:50pm).

post_text: Good morning, this is Mr. Diegel from the Kidder County School with a school update. Though we have not been informed about cancelling school beyond this week, we are making contingency plans to deliver instruction to our students through on-line instruction to the best of our ability, if the need should arise. If you do not have internet connection at your home, please call and leave a message at the school telling us your name and verifying your mailing address so we can mail your child’s educational packets. Once again, this is ONLY in the event that school is cancelled for next week, which we do not yet know. Thanks for your patience and understanding.
